      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available for acquisition is a museum-quality E92 M3, featuring the legendary S65 4.0L naturally aspirated V8. This unit delivers a visceral 8,400 RPM redline, managed by a lightning-quick 7-speed M-DCT dual-clutch transmission. The structural integrity is bolstered by the factory carbon fiber roof, significantly reducing the polar moment of inertia. Mechanically, this specimen is superlative: rod bearings and throttle actuators have been proactively replaced with upgraded components, ensuring long-term reliability. The Electronic Damper Control (EDC) system and M-Variable differential provide surgical handling precision. The exterior retains its factory luster with consistent paint-depth readings, while the interior Novillo leather remains taut with no bolster degradation. This is a definitive, turn-key example of the final naturally aspirated M3.",
